In this story, I look into how weather affects people’s moods, clothing choices, and activities based on the data I gathered from a daily weather observations survey. By analyzing temperature fluctuations, mood trends, and activity data, we can better understand the relationship between them.

How Temperature Changes Throughout the Day?

  • The first plot highlights how the average temperature fluctuates throughout the day, hour by hour.
  • It’s pretty clear that temperature shifts are predictable, with warmer hours around midday and cooler temperatures in the morning and evening.
  • People experience various temperatures, which might results in variations of activities or moods even what they wear depending on the time of day. Here’s the temperature variation throughout the day:

Conclusion

Overall, through this analysis, I’ve learned just how much the weather shapes not only our mood but also our clothing choices and activities. Whether it’s the temperature or the mood on rainy days, there’s no doubt that the weather plays a big role in how we feel and act. Adding a bit of fun through memes and creative visuals helped tell this story in a way that goes beyond just the numbers. And now, next time it’s cloudy or rainy, I’ll probably be craving hot chocolate—and that’s perfectly okay.
